SUBMISSIONS OF THE APPLICANT 

12 The applicant has submitted that costs do not always follow the event where:


 • there has been success in part by a litigant: Ruddock v Vadarlis [2001] FCA 1865 ; 115 FCR 229;
 • the public interest so warrants a departure from the usual rule: Ruddock v Vadarlis [2001] FCA 1865 ; 115 FCR 229, Oshlack [1998] HCA 11 ; 193 CLR 72;
 • the conduct of the successful party at the trial was such as to unreasonably prolong the proceedings: Ruddock v Vadarlis [2001] FCA 1865 ; 115 FCR 229.
